# CHANGELOG.md uses git's built-in union merge driver: concurrent PRs
# each insert ONE contiguous section at the fixed anchor below the
# "## Unreleased" header, and union keeps both insertions instead of
# conflicting. This ended the header-conflict treadmill where every
# merge to main re-conflicted every open PR on CHANGELOG.md alone
# (see internal_docs/changelog_workflow.md).
#
# CAVEAT: union NEVER reports a conflict — it keeps both sides of any
# overlapping edit. That is only safe for append/insert-only files.
# Never edit existing CHANGELOG lines (especially the frozen
# "## Unreleased — ..." ledger line); tests/test_changelog_structure.py
# guards the known mangling mode (duplicated header line).
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
